<p>Make sure to auto-complete the <code>@Route</code> annotation so you get the <code>use</code> statement
up top.</p>
<p>Cool!</p>
<p>Every login form looks about the same, so let's go steal some code. Google for
"Symfony security form login" and Find a page called <a href="http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookbook/security/form_login_setup.html">How to Build a Traditional Login Form</a>.</p>
<h2 id="adding-the-login-controller">Adding the Login Controller <a class="headerlink" href="rendering-login-form#adding-the-login-controller" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
