<p>This is a rare time when I <em>won't</em> bother binding my form to a class.</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p>If you're building a login form that will be used with Symfony's native <code>form_login</code>
system, override <code>getBlockPrefix()</code> and make it return an empty string. This will
put the POST data in the proper place so the <code>form_login</code> system can find it.</p>
</div><p>In <code>buildForm()</code>, let's add two things, <code>_username</code> and <code>_password</code>, which should be
a <code>PasswordType</code>:</p>
